Yip Chi Ho Hong Kong footballer

0 0

rank #4 ·

Yip Chi Ho (Chinese: 葉志豪; Jyutping: jip zi hou, born October 21, 1985 in Hong Kong) is a Hong Kong professional footballer who last played for Yuen Long as a midfielder. He moved to South China from Rangers (HKG) after the end of the 2006-07 season and represented the team in all six 2008 AFC Cup matches in the season. He was released by TSW Pegasus in 2010.
